CatDescriptText: Miss Elizabeth McCombs, children's librarian, 5219 Jordan Way, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the visit of the Russian ruler, Khrushchev, will promote world peace?" answer reads: "I'm afraid I do not. I think that the man has his own definite program which he intends to get through, regardless of whether he visits here or not.  I feel that he thinks that his program is as important to his country as we feel that our program is."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth McCombs wearing plaid v-neck dress with ruffles on shoulders, standing outside of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
